						<summary>

						<p>A slab set up in the Varadarājaperumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">(Rājarāja III ?): acc. 1216 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgāt-tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> to the temple of the god Kōdaṇḍarāmaperumāḷ. It is stated that a certain Maḻavadarayar received 8 <hi rend="italic">vēli,</hi> Virāṭarāyar 5 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> and Vattarāyar 6 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> totalling to 19 <hi rend="italic">vēli,</hi> not 20 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> as wrongly mentioned here.</p>						

						</summary>
